summary:
Recognizes the role of UN peacekeeping operations and political missions in protecting children, and reiterates its decision to include child protection provisions in their mandates (para 15);

Calls for continued implementation of the Secretary-General's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, and urges troop-contributing countries to take preventive action and ensure accountability (para 16);

Urges UN entities to give full attention to violations against children in the application of the Human Rights Due Diligence Policy (para 17);

Requests the Secretary-General to continue submitting comprehensive annual reports on the implementation of its resolutions on children and armed conflict (para 18);

Decides to remain actively seized of this matter (para 19).
